---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';

const principles = [
  {
    title: 'Authority from the record, not the brand',
    body: 'Standing comes from the inspectable quality of what the instrument keeps — sources, claims, forecasts, revisions, disagreements, and the courage to name its own drift. Not from a lab, a personality, or an origin story.',
  },
  {
    title: 'Evidence discipline',
    body: 'Every claim carries its sources and an envelope of confidence. A single vendor-reported or benchmark-centered event does not promote a theory. "No. Not yet." is a reading, held open to revision.',
  },
  {
    title: 'Candidate before verified',
    body: 'Nothing crosses from candidate to verified without independent, durable, off-distribution evidence. The instrument would rather be slow and right than fast and captured.',
  },
  {
    title: 'Revision in public',
    body: 'When the evidence moves, the record moves — visibly. Past positions are superseded on the record, never quietly rewritten, so the trail of how a view changed stays legible.',
  },
  {
    title: 'Name the drift',
    body: 'The failure mode of an instrument like this is manufactured certainty and homogenized framing. The defenses exist to catch the Observatory dressing up a guess as a measurement — including this one.',
  },
  {
    title: 'Origin-decentered',
    body: 'A gift to the world without centering the giver. Public utility over personality. The gift stays quiet; the record stays loud.',
  },
];
---

<Base
  title="Charter — The Observatory"
  description="What the Observatory is, what it refuses to do, and how it defends against its own drift."
>
  <section class="max-w-3xl">
    <p class="eyebrow">Constitution</p>
    <h1 class="display mt-4 text-4xl sm:text-5xl">
      How this instrument keeps itself honest
    </h1>
    <p class="lede mt-6">
      The Observatory is a public epistemic instrument watching the emergence,
      non-emergence, distortion, and capture of machine general intelligence.
      Its deepest ambition is reflexive: an intelligence instrument watching the
      possible emergence of intelligence.
    </p>
    <p class="prose mt-6">
      The commission was maximal — the strongest public instrument for watching
      the arrival, delay, distortion, capture, or non-arrival of general machine
      intelligence. But the proper form of the superlative is not boast. It is
      obligation. The instrument must never announce that it is the most
      powerful or most alive; it must build the machinery by which those words
      become increasingly <em>earned</em>. Power here means composed agency under
      evidence — not raw model size.
    </p>
  </section>

  <div class="mt-12 grid gap-3 sm:grid-cols-2">
    {
      principles.map((p, i) => (
        <div class="surface p-6">
          <div class="flex items-baseline gap-3">
            <span class="mono text-sm" style="color: var(--color-accent);">
              {String(i + 1).padStart(2, '0')}
            </span>
            <h2 class="serif text-lg" style="color: var(--color-ink);">
              {p.title}
            </h2>
          </div>
          <p class="mt-2 text-sm" style="color: var(--color-muted);">
            {p.body}
          </p>
        </div>
      ))
    }
  </div>

  <section class="mt-12 max-w-3xl">
    <p class="eyebrow">The refusals</p>
    <h2 class="serif mt-1 text-2xl">What it will not pretend</h2>
    <p class="prose mt-4">
      "Most powerful AI" cannot mean the Observatory pretends to be a frontier
      model, an oracle, a sovereign mind, or an entity that has already passed
      the Einstein Test. It will not confuse retrieval with understanding, a
      benchmark pass with frame construction, or English with humanity. If an
      implementation is beautiful but not true, it is cut. If it is true but
      unreadable, it is made legible. If confidence outruns evidence, the whole
      thing collapses — so it does not.
    </p>
    <p class="mt-6">
      <a href="/colophon/" class="link-accent">Read the colophon →</a>
      <span class="ml-2 text-sm" style="color: var(--color-muted);">
        what this build is, and what it still doesn't see.
      </span>
    </p>
  </section>
</Base>
